      "content": "that makes sense. so if i'm writing this, how should i handle people who argue that meritocracy is actually the most fair way to run a society and that redistribution just punishes hard work? should i just dismiss those arguments as being based on a misunderstanding of how systemic racism works, or is there a better way to frame them so they don't weaken my overall point?",
